2UzV3yzPmCKGyeVUGxLbMdq0AYQEZzkOrFx4I06-w_-qiWw4=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test metadata and classes**\\n\\nI need to clarify the status of untracked metadata, which may be anticipated as actual. I could mention that only the test file was added, but I wonder if they expect no changes to the metadata. I think our approach is fine since we didn’t touch it. There might be an issue with test class naming conventions, and I realize we need public top-level test classes. \\n\\nI’m considering making improvements, like using actual factories instead of constructing a custom loader from class names. This could help cover more ground in our tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying potential issues with metadata**\\n\\nI see potential issues with dynamic-access reports generated through library class instrumentation. While I could assert that contributions are not null, I can’t check for broader side effects. There's a question about the SpringFactoriesLoader's protected constructor possibly being deprecated, but it isn’t. \\n\\nI should avoid using internal library packages since the SpringFactoriesLoader is public. There’s also concern about the native image, where the custom loader reflects processor instantiation, and its package-private access might need adjustments. I wonder if there’s missing metadata for `getDeclaredClasses`, especially since it looks at test classes, which might not be captured appropriately.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic-access instrumentation**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the user-code-filter typically filters out caller classes or accessed classes, especially in native-image-agent scenarios. It seems to exclude library internal call sources for metadata generation. I think the dynamic-access instrumentation needs to track call site coverage without relying on the agent. \\n\\nFor reachability metadata, there might be missing pieces for declared classes in test classes when running a Native Image. If we're using Class#getDeclaredClasses(), it seems reflection metadata may be necessary for those queried declared classes.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_BzyHQljR1opI0w5uygUw6L3y|fc_0e0411bc201dcc6b016a0bd9e26a8c81a3bb77abb4135d92c6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-jackson/4.0.2/build/native/generated -type f -maxdepth 5 -print | sort | xargs -r -n1 sh -c 'echo --- $0; sed -n \"1,120p\" \"$0\"'", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1157, "output": 1466, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28223, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779161549665, "responseId": "resp_0e0411bc201dcc6b016a0bd9ce281081a3a0c1e8994300750b"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_BzyHQljR1opI0w5uygUw6L3y|fc_0e0411bc201dcc6b016a0bd9e26a8c81a3bb77abb4135d92c6", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "--- tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-jackson/4.0.2/build/native/generated/generateTestResourcesConfigFile/resource-config.json\n{\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"includes\": [],\n    \"excludes\": []\n  },\n  \"bundles\": []\n}"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779161570991}]}
